contributionDescription:
Our contributions to Optimism for which we wish to receive RetroPGF are:

⭐️ Enable developers to become builders of personalised medicine, De-Science, public goods initiatives on OP Stack; 
⭐️ Expand the utility of decentralised healthcare delivery, medicine testing & research via our OP Stack modules within OP Medicine project: 
⭐️ Evangelize N.S.U.T.’s Incubation program to create a mentorship cell for guiding and recognizing OP led public goods initiatives in medicine and healthcare;
⭐ ️ Adopt Optimism development as a part of core curriculum for students pursuing engineering courses at all levels at N.S.U.T.;
⭐️Increase in on-chain volume, user adoption and building interoperability using OP projects like Wormhole and Base.
⭐️Participate, contribute as OP builders in EthGlobal events.

impactDescription:
We wish to share the impact our contributions had on Optimism Collective:

⭐ ️ Increase in the number of Optimism developers and medical eco-system users onboarded to Optimism from 20 to 550. Pilot Deployments at Rajshri Medical College & Hospital; Covid Care Center, N.S.U.T.; S.M.S. School, Delhi;
⭐️Increase in the number of OP developers, users investing in Optimism and our key OP stack modules, health projects built on Optimism  from 10 to 490;
⭐️Improved collaboration with other key OP projects to increase the number of partner projects utilizing OP Medicine’s Web3 modules by 2 to 15;
⭐️ Bootstrap OP Stack modules into projects like Medi Assist for medical counselling and insurance, government Medical Billing platform.
⭐️Participate, contribute as OP P.G. builders in EthGlobal.
